data.enText: to send sb/sth somewhere, especially for a special purpose
Troops have been dispatched to the area.
A courier was dispatched to collect the documents.

data.chText: 发出，发送（邮件、包裹、信息）
data.enText: to send a letter, package or message somewhere

data.chText: 订单到达我方24小时内发货。
data.enText: Goods are dispatched within 24 hours of your order reaching us.

data.chText: 迅速处理；迅速办妥；迅速完成
data.enText: to deal or finish with sb/sth quickly and completely

data.chText: 他连续几盘迅速击败了那位比他年轻的选手。
data.enText: He dispatched the younger player in straight sets.
to kill a person or an animal
the act of sending sb/sth somewhere

data.chText: 更多的食品供应已备妥即刻发运。
data.enText: More food supplies are ready for immediate dispatch.

data.chText: （军事人员或政府官员之间的）急件，快信
data.enText: a message or report sent quickly from one military officer to another or between government officials

data.chText: （驻外国记者发给报刊的）新闻报道，电讯
data.enText: a report sent to a newspaper by a journalist who is working in a foreign country

means: 发出，发送(邮件、包裹、信息)
(军事人员或政府官员之间的)急件，快信
(驻外国记者发给报刊的)新闻报道，电讯

ex.chText: 一队医生被派往非洲提供医疗服务。
ex.enText: A group of doctors were dispatched to Africa to provide medical service.

ex.chText: 派了两架直升飞机去救援伤者。
ex.enText: Two helicopters were dispatched to rescue the injured.

synonyms.bx: 指为达到某个特殊目的而将某人或某物送到某地。

ex.chText: 这批电视机将于明天送到代理商处。
ex.enText: The TV sets will be consigned to the agent tomorrow.

ex.chText: 将上述货物以快件发送。
ex.enText: Consign the said goods by express mail.

synonyms.bx: 尤指为了进行销售将某物运至某地。

ex.chText: 回家的路上记得把信寄出去。
ex.enText: Remember to post the letter on your way home.
He was posted to London in 2010.

synonyms.bx: 指通过邮局寄送物品，也指被派往某地工作一段时间，作后者解时通常用被动语态。

ex.chText: 我们把那台冰箱退给厂家了。
ex.enText: We sent the fridge back to the manufacturer.

ex.chText: 你收到我上星期给你寄的信了吗？
ex.enText: Did you get the letter I sent to you last week?

ex.chText: 贝丝被送进了私立学校。
ex.enText: Beth was sent to private school.

synonyms.bx: 普通用词，指发送或寄送某物，也指吩咐或安排某人去某地。

tr: the act of sending off something
the property of being prompt and efficient
an official report (usually sent in haste)

example: the traitor was dispatched by the conspirators

tr: send away towards a designated goal
dispose of rapidly and without delay and efficiently
example: He dispatched the task he was assigned
The mafia boss ordered his enemies murdered

value.boxr_value: in BRIT, also use 英国英语亦用 despatch

value.def: If you dispatch someone to a place, you send them there for a particular reason.

example.ex: The Italian government was preparing to dispatch 4,000 soldiers to search the island.
example.tran: 意大利政府正准备派遣 4,000 名士兵搜索该岛。

example.ex: The despatch of the task force is purely a contingency measure.
example.tran: 派出特遣部队纯粹是应急之举。

value.def: If you dispatch a message, letter, or parcel, you send it to a particular person or destination.

example.ex: The victory inspired him to dispatch a gleeful telegram to Roosevelt...
example.tran: 胜利促使他给罗斯福发了封喜报。

example.ex: Free gifts are dispatched separately so please allow 28 days for delivery.
example.tran: 赠品会分开发送，所以请预留28天的送货期。

example.ex: We have 125 cases ready for dispatch.

value.tran: 发送，发出（信息、信件或包裹）

value.def: A dispatch is a special report that is sent to a newspaper or broadcasting organization by a journalist who is in a different town or country.

example.ex: ...this despatch from our West Africa correspondent.
example.tran: 我台驻西非记者发来的这一报道

value.tran: (身在另一城市或国家的记者发送的)电讯，新闻报道

value.def: A dispatch is a message or report that is sent, for example, by army officers or government officials to their headquarters.

example.ex: I was carrying dispatches from the ambassador.

defx.def: If a soldier is mentioned in dispatches, he or she is considered to have been extremely brave in a battle, and is recommended for a medal.

example.ex: He was hailed as a hero, mentioned in dispatches and finally given a medal.
example.tran: 他被誉为英雄，得到了通报表彰，最后还获得了一枚勋章。

value.tran: (军官或政府官员发送给总部的)急件，快信

value.def: To dispatch a person or an animal means to kill them.

example.ex: The fox takes his chance with a pack of hounds which may catch him and despatch him immediately.
example.tran: 那只狐狸和一群随时可能置其于死地的猎狗冒险周旋。

value.def: To dispatch a job or task means to finish it quickly and efficiently without wasting time.

example.ex: Amy sat outside in the sun while Gerald despatched his business.
example.tran: 埃米坐在外面晒太阳，而杰拉尔德则忙着处理个人事务。

value.def: If you do something with dispatch, you do it very quickly.

example.ex: He feels we should act with despatch.
example.tran: 他觉得我们应该迅速行动。

trans: 调度中心；派件中心；派遣中心
负载配电；负载等；负载等,负载配电；负荷分配
